                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17160113-38-victim210 t17160113-38-viclabel201"></join>, she us'd, when he was upon Duty, to go to Bed to his Wife, with which he was pretty well contented but what vex'd him was, that she would not get up when he wanted to get in; and that she would lie in Bed with him after his Wife was up. But one Night, his Wife had occasion to tell some Money out of a Bag, and left 32 s. in it, which she put into her Husband's Pocket before he went to Bed; who next Morning felt for it and missing it, thought his Wife might take it out again, and went contentedly about his Business; but coming home, a great Search was made, and at last the Money was found under the Bed, in a Place where they had look'd three or four times before. The Jury considering the Matter, <rs id="t17160113-38-verdict202" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17160113-38-verdict202" type="verdictCategory" value="notGuilty"></interp>
